<span id="freeTextContainer2678698531288030288">When my husband found out this book was coming out he says <br/>&quot;Is that by the same person who wrote that book you sat on the couch laughing while reading?&quot;<br/>&quot;Yes, yes it is.&quot;<br/>&quot;Ugh.&quot;<br/><br/><br/>Much to his pleasure, this book had the same effect. He&apos;s the Victor of my world but I suspect if a third book rolls around he&apos;ll make me vacate the room and read it elsewhere. I truly have never laughed so much while reading as I have while reading both of her books. <br/><br/>Jenny is a magical unicorn of a human and I strongly enc</span>
  <span id="freeText2678698531288030288" style="display:none">When my husband found out this book was coming out he says <br />"Is that by the same person who wrote that book you sat on the couch laughing while reading?"<br />"Yes, yes it is."<br />"Ugh."<br /><br /><br />Much to his pleasure, this book had the same effect. He's the Victor of my world but I suspect if a third book rolls around he'll make me vacate the room and read it elsewhere. I truly have never laughed so much while reading as I have while reading both of her books. <br /><br />Jenny is a magical unicorn of a human and I strongly encourage you read her books. If you or someone you know struggles with mental illness, if you just want to giggle, or if you're a grumpy tightwad who maybe just needs to lighten up a little this book is for you. <br /><br />But also read her first book, <a href="https://www.goodreads.com/book/show/12868761.Let_s_Pretend_This_Never_Happened_A_Mostly_True_Memoir" title="Let's Pretend This Never Happened A Mostly True Memoir by Jenny Lawson" rel="nofollow noopener">Let's Pretend This Never Happened: A Mostly True Memoir</a> because it's also great and there's some hilarious shit in there and some references you'd probably not want to miss. And her blog. Cause that's where it all started, and where it continues to be awesome in between books. </span>
