<div id="review_1293860229" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1293860229" />
    <a title="Kelly" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2044432-kelly"><img alt="Kelly" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1466627389p2/2044432.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1293860229?book_show_action=true">May 30, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kelly" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kelly" href="/user/show/2044432-kelly">Kelly</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2044432-kelly?shelf=abandoned">abandoned</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2044432-kelly?shelf=2016">2016</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1293860229" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13030174724677518548">I was really excited to read this book, and completely shocked at how much I disliked it. The introduction was beautiful-- emotionally raw, vulnerable, touching. It felt like an honest look at the struggles of living with mental illness. And then the actual book started. To me, the content of the book seemed like the frenetic and trivial rambling of a manic pixie dream girl on crack. It felt like Lawson was just doing everything in her power to distract herself from her laundry list of mental il</span>
  <span id="freeText13030174724677518548" style="display:none">I was really excited to read this book, and completely shocked at how much I disliked it. The introduction was beautiful-- emotionally raw, vulnerable, touching. It felt like an honest look at the struggles of living with mental illness. And then the actual book started. To me, the content of the book seemed like the frenetic and trivial rambling of a manic pixie dream girl on crack. It felt like Lawson was just doing everything in her power to distract herself from her laundry list of mental illness and to take the reader along for the ride. Don't get me wrong, I really get what it's like to not ever want to get out of bed from depression and anxiety. I just know that for me, distracting myself with addiction to excitement doesn't fix all that shit, it merely makes it worse. I had just hoped that this book would be a combination of humor and honesty around mental health issues rather than how cute it is that she has a stuffed raccoon that she uses to annoy her husband. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13030174724677518548" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


