<div id="review_2863585104" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2863585104" />
    <a title="Ines" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/43642795-ines"><img alt="Ines" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1542692123p2/43642795.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2863585104?book_show_action=true">Jun 20, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Ines" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Ines" href="/user/show/43642795-ines">Ines</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2863585104" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15516210895214872813">Never laughed so hard reading a series of exagerations and suspicious fibs as you will find them exposed here.... What people won’t do for money...wow... I should get published all the crazy that comes out of the mouths of my actually “crazy&quot; patients. Silly me, we really could have made a lot of money in the institution where I work..... and then rearrange things, create new monitored housing, buy new materials, invite new specialists to develop new rehabilitative therapies.... Shame on us who </span>
  <span id="freeText15516210895214872813" style="display:none">Never laughed so hard reading a series of exagerations and suspicious fibs as you will find them exposed here.... What people won’t do for money...wow... I should get published all the crazy that comes out of the mouths of my actually “crazy" patients. Silly me, we really could have made a lot of money in the institution where I work..... and then rearrange things, create new monitored housing, buy new materials, invite new specialists to develop new rehabilitative therapies.... Shame on us who were born in Italy, brought up to think that certain things are not to be done or even thought about, slaves of the concept "no to the exploitation of the misfortunes of others.. <br />A concentration of exagerated nonsenses I thought I couldn’t read them by Americans, I’m not saying they don’t make you laugh...... but wow, this chick will be a cronic bipolar but not stupid...<br /> this "marketing" depression was worth it!!! ( i bet it really!!)<br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />."Hahahahahah!!! penso di non aver mai riso cosi tanto leggendo una serie di fregnacce e balle a raffica come le troverete esposte qui dentro....<br />Cosa non si fa per soldi, caspiterina, dovrei far pubblicare tutte le pazzie e le follie che escono dalla bocca dei miei pazienti veramente "matti".<br />Vedete come siamo scemi nell'istituto dove lavoro.....avremo potuto fare soldi a palate, indi risistemare un sacco di cose, creare nuovi alloggi abitativi monitorati, nuovo materiale, invitare nuovi specialisti per creare nuovi percorsi riabilitativi....<br />Mannaggia a noi che nati in Italia, e tutti cresciuti che certe cose non si fanno e neanche si pensano, schiavi del concetto "no allo sfruttamento delle disgrazie altrui..."<br />Un concentrato di assurdità in salsa pecoreccia pensavo di non poterle leggere per bocca di americani, non dico che non facciano ridere...... ma caspita, sta tipa sarà psicotica ma mica scema...<br />viva la commercializzazione (monetizzazione) della depressione!!! e un brindisi ai suoi soldi buoni.</span>
  <a data-text-id="15516210895214872813" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
